<br>
35$ US at Gamestop.<br>
<br>
The macro would appear like this:<br>
<br>
press 1<br>
delay 0.10<br>
release 1<br>
delay 3.0<br>
press 2<br>
delay 0.10<br>
release 2<br>
delay 3.0<br>
press 3<br>
delay 0.10 <br>
release 3<br>
<br>
Then on the right side there is a drop down that will allow you to select play macro once, play till you stop it, and one other option. You just select play till stopped, then make a key that you program to be the &quot;cancel macro&quot; (this is an option at configuration) which stops the macro dead in its tracks. I bought one of these about 2 months ago and it is the best thing that ever happened to EQ for me, it took away one of the things I have hated most for almost 4 years now. <br>
<br>
You can then set up different macro song sets with different delays. For example, if I am raiding in ssra (for me this is insane lag) I can reliably twist 3 songs if I make the btw press/release delay 0.25 seconds and the btw song delay 3.25 seconds. I may miss notes (which the macro will not see or correct it just misses and continues on its way) but at least it takes 95% of the frustration out of high lag encounters as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fleetnotedirgestrider>Fleetnote Dirgestrider</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#330000>(7/7/04 9:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19562.topic&index=51>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ~</span><hr size=1> The Nostromo has a way to program macros. This is the only SOE approved way of making macros, other programs are still against the EULA. For whatever reason SOE has said that game pad macroing is ok.<br>
<br>
You set up the macro in the Nostromo's little utility. Basicly you tell it what buttons to hit and add any delays you would like. When in game you hit one of the Nostromo's buttons and it will feed EQ the buttons. The macro can be as long as you want and it has options for repeating.<br>
<br>
If set up right you can make it twist as many songs as you wish. I have found that I can keep four songs up in my song box (I realize this does not necessarily mean the songs are actually in effect). If you are not too worried about songs dropping due to missed notes and such it works quite well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jimmayjam>Jimmay Jam</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 413<br> <font color=#330000>(7/7/04 9:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19562.topic&index=52>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://userpic.livejournal.com/3740691/162948 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ~</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Now do like Jimmay and tell me I spelled my sig wrong every time I have posted on this board, even though I have been hand typing it every time please.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
